WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.400
Hi, I'm Max Kuhn, I work at Posit.

00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:13.080
I'm here to entice you into joining us at the Advanced Tidymodels Workshop at our conference.

00:00:13.080 --> 00:00:16.639
Now it says advanced in the title, you don't need to be an expert to join us.

00:00:16.639 --> 00:00:20.520
If you've taken the introductory tidymodels workshop, you'd be in a really good position

00:00:20.520 --> 00:00:21.719
to join us.

00:00:21.719 --> 00:00:25.639
But if you haven't, if you've ever used tidymodels before, you'll probably be in good shape.

00:00:25.639 --> 00:00:30.400
So if you've fit a parsnip model or resampled it, or if you've used a recipe, things like

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:35.119
that, you'll probably be in a good position to understand what we're going to go through.

00:00:35.119 --> 00:00:37.540
Now what are we going to talk about at the conference?

00:00:37.540 --> 00:00:40.560
So one thing we'll talk about is advanced recipe usage.

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:44.360
So recipes are like pre-processors for your data before you put them in the model.

00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:47.639
And we'll talk about some sort of like pro tips for using recipes, as well as how to

00:00:47.639 --> 00:00:49.360
optimize them.

00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:51.959
The second thing we'll talk about is model tuning.

00:00:51.959 --> 00:00:53.520
So you have models and some tuning parameters.

00:00:53.520 --> 00:00:58.680
We'll look at things like grid search, iterative search, some cool things called racing methods

00:00:58.680 --> 00:01:00.680
that you can use to optimize your model performance.

00:01:00.680 --> 00:01:04.199
And then the third thing we'll talk about is calibration.

00:01:04.199 --> 00:01:08.239
So after you fit your model, you want to make sure that your classification probabilities

00:01:08.239 --> 00:01:13.000
or your fitted regression predictions are super consistent with the data that you built

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:14.000
the model on.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.440
And so we have some new tools for that that we think are really cool.

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:21.160
So anyway, we hope to see you in person in Chicago, and especially hope to see you at

00:01:21.360 --> 00:01:22.360
the EDS signals workshop.

00:01:22.360 --> 00:01:22.860
Thanks a lot.

